# Network: Clients 192.0.2.10 and 192.0.2.20 share virtual destination
# 203.0.113.50 but are assigned isolated backends 10.10.0.10 and 10.20.0.20.
# Policy: Source-sensitive rules rewrite only the destination to the matching backend.
# Topology: id.
# Property first-delivery: The first client reaches its assigned backend.
# Property second-delivery: The second client reaches its assigned backend.
# Property first-cannot-cross: The first client cannot reach the second backend.
# Property second-cannot-cross: The second client cannot reach the first backend.
# Property broad-destination: With source unconstrained, some virtual-IP packet reaches either backend.
# Property source-preserved: The first client's source address survives delivery.
policy =
    (filter(src_ip = 192.0.2.10 & dst_ip = 203.0.113.50) . dst_ip <- 10.10.0.10)
  + (filter(src_ip = 192.0.2.20 & dst_ip = 203.0.113.50) . dst_ip <- 10.20.0.20);
topology = id;
check first-delivery: src_ip = 192.0.2.10 & dst_ip = 203.0.113.50 => dst_ip = 10.10.0.10;
check second-delivery: src_ip = 192.0.2.20 & dst_ip = 203.0.113.50 => dst_ip = 10.20.0.20;
check first-cannot-cross: src_ip = 192.0.2.10 & dst_ip = 203.0.113.50 => dst_ip = 10.20.0.20;
check second-cannot-cross: src_ip = 192.0.2.20 & dst_ip = 203.0.113.50 => dst_ip = 10.10.0.10;
check broad-destination: dst_ip = 203.0.113.50 => dst_ip = 10.10.0.10 | dst_ip = 10.20.0.20;
check source-preserved: src_ip = 192.0.2.10 & dst_ip = 203.0.113.50 => src_ip = 192.0.2.10 & dst_ip = 10.10.0.10;
